                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d696">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.796A/4–1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-14T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 14, 1948—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>905. Re Condes 187 Apr 12.<note n="10" xml:id="d696fn10">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> Dept and CAA holding preliminary
                    discussions re staff of mission and procurement of equipment. More definite info
                    will be forwarded Consulate General within 2 or 3 weeks. Sent Shanghai as Dept’s
                    905 repeated Nanking as 727.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
